<task id="AIPU-057" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Welcome experience with guided prompt buttons for no-context launch</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <wave>5E</wave>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui, ux</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>AIPU-040</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    When Spaarke AI opens from main navigation with no entity context, the chat pane shows
    an empty SprkChat with no guidance. Create a welcome experience that helps users
    understand what they can do and guides them to their first action.

    The welcome state replaces the empty chat when there is no active session and no entity
    context. It includes:
    1. A branded header ("Welcome to Spaarke AI")
    2. Prompt buttons for common workflows: Analyze a Document, Research, Financial Analysis, Draft
    3. A "Recent" section showing the user's last 3-5 chat sessions (from chat history)
    4. When the user clicks a prompt button, it injects a structured first message into SprkChat
       (e.g., clicking "Analyze a Document" sends the message "I want to analyze a document")
    5. The welcome state disappears once a chat session starts

    Design requirements:
    - Use Fluent v9 Card components for prompt buttons with icons
    - Responsive grid layout (2x2 on desktop, single column on narrow)
    - Dark mode support (ADR-021 — semantic tokens only)
    - The prompt buttons should be configurable (array of {label, icon, message})
    - Recent sessions should show title, entity context badge, and relative timestamp
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior frontend developer with React 19 and Fluent v9 experience</role>

  <goal>
    When Spaarke AI opens with no context, users see a welcoming guided experience instead
    of an empty chat. Prompt buttons inject first messages that kick off specific workflows.
    Recent sessions allow quick resumption.
  </goal>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ChatPanel.tsx</file>
    <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/LeftPane.tsx</file>
    <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/chat-history/ChatHistoryPanel.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Context/src/providers/StandaloneAiContext.tsx</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">All UI must use Fluent v9 semantic tokens — no hardcoded colors</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Dark mode must work without additional CSS</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Prompt buttons inject messages into SprkChat — they do NOT call BFF directly</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Welcome state must disappear once a session starts (chatSessionId becomes non-null)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/theme-consistency.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Create WelcomePanel component with branded header and prompt button grid</step>
    <step order="2">Define prompt button configuration array with label, icon, and injected message</step>
    <step order="3">Add recent sessions section using ChatApiClient to fetch last 5 sessions</step>
    <step order="4">Wire WelcomePanel into LeftPane/ChatPanel — show when no session and no entity context</step>
    <step order="5">When prompt button clicked, call SprkChat's send message API or set initial message</step>
    <step order="6">Verify dark mode renders correctly</step>
    <step order="7">Build and verify: npm run build</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Welcome panel renders when Spaarke AI opens with no entity context</criterion>
    <criterion>4 prompt buttons visible with icons and labels</criterion>
    <criterion>Clicking a prompt button starts a chat with the injected message</criterion>
    <criterion>Recent sessions section shows last 3-5 sessions with metadata</criterion>
    <criterion>Welcome panel disappears once chat session starts</criterion>
    <criterion>Dark mode renders correctly</criterion>
    <criterion>npm run build passes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
